. Local Variables

Definition: Variables declared inside a function.

Scope: Accessible only within the function where they are declared.

Persistence: Values are temporary and disappear after function execution.

Example:
//SPDX-License-Identifier: MIT

pragma solidity ^0.8.0;

contract local { 

    function store () pure public returns (uint){
    uint age = 10;
    string memory name = "harshita";
    return age;
    }
    
}
  
